cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper describes the use of a convolutional neural network for automatic detection and classification of coronary artery plaque and stenosis in coronary CT angiography. This involves image analysis and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a recurrent neural network for feature aggregation suggests the involvement of natural language processing (cs.NE) techniques. Finally, the use of medical imaging data suggests the involvement of multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
